article.headline: James Madison 72, Dartmouth 57
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Abdulai Jalloh scored 22 points and Terrance Carter added 14 as James Madison beat Dartmouth 72-57 on Saturday night. Dartmouth (1-2) held a slim 25-24 lead late in the first half, but the Dukes (2-0) closed the half with a 13-4 run to take a 37-29 halftime lead. Alex Barnett scored 20 points to lead the Big Green, while DeVon Mosley had 12 and Johnathan Ball added 11 points and 10 rebounds. Dartmouth shot 41 percent from the floor and held a 33-27 advantage in rebounds.
